# Copy to .env and fill in real values. Never commit .env.
#
# RECOMMENDED (multi-device setup, P6.5): put the canonical secrets in Google
# Drive (A-Wiki-Data/secrets/env-wastewater-webapp.env) and make the local
# .env a one-line stub:
#   __LOAD_FROM_DRIVE__=true
# The resolver (scripts/_env.py) then reads the Drive file on every machine.
# See CONTRIBUTING.md "Secret storage across devices" for full setup.
#
# (Backend-era vars — SUPABASE_DB_URL, JWT secret, AUTH_MODE — left with the
# FastAPI app on the archive/fastapi-backend branch. The frontend's VITE_*
# vars live in frontend/.env, not here.)

# Supabase Personal Access Token — used by scripts/apply_migration_api.py and
# scripts/introspect_schema_api.py to reach ENV_DB over HTTPS (Management API,
# IPv6 workaround). Generate at:
#   https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=
